  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "P.T.Oは、コーエーによる別の軍事シミュレーションゲームです。このゲームでは、日本または連合国のいずれかを選択できます。艦隊を管理し、新しい軍艦を発注することで、紛争のさまざまな側面を制御できます。（艦船の開発、基地防衛、艦隊編成、直接戦闘の指揮、経済的決定）P.T.Oには多くのプレイオプションがあり、数々の有名な戦闘のいずれかを選んでプレイすることも、キャンペーンを進めることもできます。一方の陣営または両方を制御することが可能です。また、勝利条件に関しても限られたコントロールがあります。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "P.T.O. (Pacific Theater of Operations), released as Teitoku no Ketsudan (提督の決断) in Japan, is a console strategy video game released by Koei. It was originally released for the PC-9801 in 1989 and had been ported to various platforms, such as the X68000, FM Towns, PC-8801 (1990), MSX2 (1991), Sega Genesis and the Super NES (both in 1992). Players could assume one side of the Pacific Theater of Operations during World War II, acting as naval commander, organizing fleets, building new ships, appropriating supplies and fuel, and even engaging in diplomacy with other countries. The player can choose one of several World War Two battles to simulate, or could control the entire Pacific campaign well before the Japanese attack on Pearl Harbor.\nA sequel, P.T.O. II, was released by Koei in 1993. Teitoku no Ketsudan III (P.T.O. III) was never released outside Japan, but a P.T.O. IV was released for the PlayStation 2 in the US and Europe.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
  ],
  "first_release_date": "1992-09-24",
